answers.body_markdown:
What you&#39;re describing is called banding. For some reason, the LibGDX default frame buffer on Android only uses 16 bit color. You can change it to 32 bit like this in your AndroidLauncher:

	protected void onCreate (Bundle savedInstanceState) {
		super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
		AndroidApplicationConfiguration config = new AndroidApplicationConfiguration(){{
			r = 8;
			g = 8;
			b = 8;
			a = 8;
		}};
		initialize(new MyGdxGame(), config);
	}

You can also enable dithering to reduce banding, but there might be a performance hit. For what it&#39;s worth, I always keep it on and all my stuff runs at 60fps, so I think it would take a fairly heavy game for it to become problem.

To enable dithering, put this in your game&#39;s `create()` method:

    Gdx.gl.glEnable(GL20.GL_DITHER);

